article.headline: Campbell 75, Chicago St. 69
article.story: CHICAGO -- Darren White scored 25 points Monday night to lead Campbell to a 75-69 victory over Chicago State. Eric Griffin added 17 points for the Camels (4-0), with Trey Freeman contributing 12 and Rico Ferguson 10. Freeman added nine rebounds and six assists. Clarke Rosenberg came off the bench to lead the Cougars (0-4) with 19 points. Jeremy Robinson scored 18, and Lee Fisher had 17 points and a game-high 12 rebounds. Campbell shot 51.2 percent (22 of 43) and 54.5 percent (6 of 11) from 3-point distance. The Camels never trailed and were up 66-52 with 2:15 to play. They led 73-61 with 46 seconds left before the Cougars quickly ran off eight in a row to trim it to 73-69. But White hit two free throws to finish it.
